title: Armies & Leaders (The Photographic History of the Civil War)
description:
The Fairfax Press | 1983 | 0517411458 | English | 328 pages | PDF | 55.8 MB

This fascinating volume profiles the leaders from both sides of the Civil War and analyzes the makeup of the armies that comprised the fighting ranks. Its unique collection of more than 200 black-and-white photographs takes the reader into the campsites and onto the battlefields where victories were won and lives were lost. The superb text and detailed descriptions of the photographs present an authoritative yet sensitive portrayal of the War Between the States
